    • Method Detail

      • getMap

        <K,V> DMap<K,V> getMap(String name)
        Replies the DMap with the given name.

        This function permits to create a map for keys without a natural order, and without a specific comparator. An object has a natural order if it implements Comparable.

        This function is equivalent to create a HashMap in the standard Java API. If the keys have a natural order, i.e. they implement the Comparable interface, or if you are able to provide a Comparator, then it is recommended to use getMap(String, Comparator) in place of the function getMap(String).

        Type Parameters:
        K - - types of the keys in the map.
        V - - types of the values in the map.
        Parameters:
        name - - name of the shared map.
        Returns:
        the map.
        See Also:
        getMap(String, Comparator)

      • getMap

        <K,V> DMap<K,V> getMap(String name,
                       Comparator<? super K> comparator)
        Replies the DMap with the given name.

        This function permits to create a map for keys with a natural order, OR with a specific comparator. An object has a natural order if it implements Comparable. If the comparator is null, then the natural order of the keys is used.

        This function is equivalent to create a TreeMap in the standard Java API. If the keys have not a natural order, i.e. they not implement the Comparable interface, or if you are not able to provide a Comparator, then it is recommended to use getMap(String) in place of the function getMap(String, Comparator).

        Type Parameters:
        K - - types of the keys in the map.
        V - - types of the values in the map.
        Parameters:
        name - - name of the shared map.
        comparator - - the comparator of the keys.
        Returns:
        the map.
        See Also:
        getMap(String)
